fields.title: Cosmic Veggie Stir-Fry
fields.description: A quick and colorful vegetable stir-fry with a tangy soy-ginger sauce, perfect for weeknights.
fields.ingredients:
1 tbsp olive oil
1 bell pepper, sliced
1 carrot, julienned
1 zucchini, sliced
1 cup broccoli florets
1/4 cup soy sauce
1 tbsp ginger, minced
1 tbsp garlic, minced
1 tsp sesame seeds
fields.steps:
1. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
2. Add minced garlic and ginger, sautéing for about 1 minute until fragrant.
3. Toss in the bell pepper, carrot, zucchini, and broccoli. Stir-fry for 5-7 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
4. Pour in the soy sauce, stirring everything to coat evenly.
5. Sprinkle sesame seeds on top, give it one last stir, and serve warm. Enjoy your veggie adventure!

fields.title: Space Traveler's Chicken Wrap
fields.description: A protein-packed chicken wrap with creamy avocado and crunchy veggies, ideal for a meal on the go.
fields.ingredients:
• 1 whole-wheat tortilla
• 1/2 cup cooked chicken breast, shredded
• 1/4 avocado, sliced
• 1/4 cup lettuce, chopped
• 1/4 cup cucumber, sliced
• 1 tbsp Greek yogurt
• Salt and pepper to taste
fields.steps:
1. Lay the whole-wheat tortilla flat on a clean surface.
2. Spread Greek yogurt across the center.
3. Layer shredded chicken, avocado, lettuce, and cucumber evenly on the tortilla.
4. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
5. Roll up the tortilla, tucking in the edges as you go, and wrap it tightly.
6. Slice in half if desired, and take it with you on your next interstellar journey!

fields.title: Martian Meatballs
fields.description: Juicy and flavorful meatballs with a hint of garlic and herbs, baked to perfection.
fields.ingredients:
• 1 lb ground beef or turkey
• 1/4 cup breadcrumbs
• 1 egg
• 1 tsp garlic powder
• 1 tsp Italian seasoning
• Salt and pepper to taste
fields.steps:
1. Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).
2. In a large mixing bowl, combine the ground beef or turkey, breadcrumbs, egg, garlic powder, Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper.
3. Shape the mixture into small meatballs, about 1 inch in diameter.
4. Place the meatballs on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
5. Bake for 15-20 minutes or until browned and cooked through.
6. Serve hot and enjoy your Martian morsels!

fields.title: Galactic Greek Salad
fields.description: A fresh, vibrant salad with a zesty vinaigrette, featuring classic Mediterranean ingredients.
fields.ingredients:
• 1 cup cucumber, chopped
• 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved
• 1/4 cup feta cheese, crumbled
• 1/4 cup Kalamata olives, pitted
• 1 tbsp olive oil
• 1 tbsp lemon juice
• Salt and pepper to taste
fields.steps:
1. In a large bowl, combine chopped cucumber, cherry tomatoes, feta cheese, and Kalamata olives.
2. Drizzle olive oil and lemon juice over the salad.
3. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
4. Gently toss everything together until evenly coated.
5. Serve immediately and savor the fresh Mediterranean vibes!

fields.title: Interstellar Salmon Bowl
fields.description: A hearty bowl of salmon, rice, and veggies, drizzled with a lemon-herb sauce.
fields.ingredients:
• 1 salmon fillet (4 oz)
• 1/2 cup cooked brown rice
• 1/4 cup broccoli, steamed
• 1/4 cup carrots, steamed
• 1 tbsp lemon juice
• 1 tsp dill
fields.steps:
1. Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).
2. Place the salmon fillet on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
3. Drizzle lemon juice over the salmon and sprinkle with dill.
4. Bake for 12-15 minutes, or until the salmon flakes easily with a fork.
5. Meanwhile, prepare your bowl by adding cooked brown rice, steamed broccoli, and steamed carrots.
6. Place the baked salmon on top, and your interstellar fuel is ready to go!

fields.title: Planetary Pasta Primavera
fields.description: A light pasta dish with fresh vegetables and a garlic-lemon sauce, perfect for a comforting yet healthy meal.
fields.ingredients:
• 1 cup whole wheat pasta
• 1/4 cup cherry tomatoes, halved
• 1/4 cup zucchini, sliced
• 1/4 cup bell pepper, sliced
• 1 tbsp olive oil
• 1 clove garlic, minced
• 1 tbsp Parmesan cheese
• Salt and pepper to taste
fields.steps:
1. Cook the whole wheat pasta according to package instructions. Drain and set aside.
2. In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.
3. Add minced garlic and sauté for 1 minute until fragrant.
4. Add cherry tomatoes, zucchini, and bell pepper, cooking for 5-6 minutes until tender.
5. Add the cooked pasta to the skillet and toss everything together.
6. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, season with salt and pepper, and serve your fresh, vibrant dish!
